Package: linuxcloth
Version: @VERSION@
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Shiinamachi <shiinamachi@users.noreply.github.com>
Installed-Size: @INSTALLED_SIZE@
Homepage: https://github.com/shiinamachi/linuxcloth
Depends: bubblewrap, ca-certificates, hicolor-icon-theme, libc6, libfontconfig1, libfreetype6, libgcc-s1, libgssapi-krb5-2, libice6, libicu | libicu72 | libicu74 | libicu75 | libicu76 | libicu77 | libicu78, libsm6, libssl3 | libssl3t64, libstdc++6, libx11-6, libxcb1, libxext6, libxfixes3, libxi6, libxrandr2, ovmf, passt, qemu-system-gui, qemu-system-x86, qemu-utils, swtpm, swtpm-tools, tzdata, virt-viewer, zlib1g
Recommends: wimtools, xdg-desktop-portal, xorriso
Description: Disposable Windows catalog launcher for Linux
 linuxcloth provides a Linux-native catalog UI and command-line interface that
 launch user-provided Windows installations in disposable QEMU/KVM sessions.
 It does not include Windows media, product keys, or generated virtual-machine
 images.
